          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A natural uranium foil was irradiated",
                "for 63 min in an external beam of 28 GeV protons from",
                "the Alternating Gradient Synchrotron at Brookhaven",
                "National Laboratory. The intensity of the beam",
                "striking the target was determined by measuring the",
                "yields of 22Na and 24Na in a 12.72 mg/cm2 Al foil",
                "irradiated simultaneously with the U foil. Following",
                "a one day delay for shipment of the irradiated foils",
                "to the Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory, analysis of the",
                "radioactivities of the target fragments began. The",
                "irradiated U foil and the mylar catcher foils were",
                "cut approximately in half; the target was counted",
                "before and after the cutting process, allowing an",
                "exact determination of the relative fractions. one",
                "half of the target and its associated mylar catcher",
                "foils were subjected to direct gamma-ray spectroscopy,",
                "while a chemical group separation procedure was",
                "applied to the other 33.5 mg/cm2 U foil half without",
                "its catcher foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
